comments.body:
Ok, I tried it on Ubuntu 16.04.

Linking using {{/usr/bin/ld}}, with cold ccache:
{code}
real	0m39.552s
user	5m44.365s
sys	0m26.581s
{code}

Linking using {{/usr/bin/gold}}, with cold ccache:
{code}
real	0m39.390s
user	5m25.619s
sys	0m25.656s
{code}

Linking using {{/usr/bin/ld}}, with warm ccache:
{code}
real	0m12.148s
user	0m50.797s
sys	0m9.527s
{code}

Linking using {{/usr/bin/gold}}, with warm ccache:
{code}
real	0m10.990s
user	0m29.445s
sys	0m7.947s
{code}

So this means we'd save ~20 seconds of CPU time on each build. By the way, I tested this by adding the following line to the CMake scripts (works with clang, I'm not sure about gcc):
{code}
set(CXX_COMMON_FLAGS "${CXX_COMMON_FLAGS} -fuse-ld=gold")
{code}
